	<TABLE><TR><TD><IMG SRC="graphics/button.gif" ALIGN="TOP"></TD><TD><FONT FACE=" Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" SIZE=+1 COLOR="#000000"><A NAME="200012303I"><B>Big site changes underway</B></A></FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN="left"><FONT FACE=" Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" SIZE=+1 COLOR="#000000">2000-05-02</FONT></TD><TD></TD></TR></TABLE><TABLE><TR><TD><FONT FACE=" Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" SIZE=2 COLOR="#000000">Updates to the site today...<BR><BR>
<B>Kunark Daily Image:</B><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Ariel">
You will notice a lot of changes on the main page. Foremost is the addition of a new feature called "Kunark Daily Image". I will be updating this daily starting tomorrow, showcasing some great images captured from Kunark! I am looking for submissions to post… so if you are currently exploring Kunark, and come across a nice photographic opportunity, please take some time to cap a shot and submit it <A HREF="mailto:madwand@home.com?subject=Kunark%20Shots">Here</A>.<BR><BR>

Here are some basic guidelines for what I am looking for…<BR><BR>

High quality JPEGS (low compression/high quality) of screen resolutions 800 x 600 or above in full screen mode with no menus or text. I am looking for unique images showing great content (new cities… awe inspiring landscapes… fearsome new monsters… etc). I am not looking for funny pictures of bugs, graphic glitches or anything else like that. I can't promise I will post everything I receive, but I will review them all and post the ones I feel are nice, giving credit to the submitter in the heading.<BR><BR>

Other changes we are working on include the addition of a Polling feature to the main page, and automatic posting of the latest news articles. The polling feature is still under construction so please ignore it for now. We will announce when it is fully operational. <FONT COLOR="#ff0000"> ( The Polling feature is now fully operational )</FONT>
<BR><BR>

<A HREF="maps.php3"><B>Maps:</B></A><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">
Major update to the Atlas today! I completely redid all the graphics and image maps to make it possible to browse through our extensive library of maps graphically. All continents and planes are represented now, and adding any new maps is as easy as a few mouse clicks for me *grin*. In addition, over the last couple of days I have collected 18 new maps… including 10 from the new land of Kunark. We now have a grand total of 219 maps in our library! Here is the list of additions…<BR><BR>

<A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Burning%20Wood"><B>1. </B>Burning Wood</A> - by Hoppas Ovale.<BR>
<A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Firiona"><B>2. </B>Firiona Vie</A> - 2 different maps of the High Eleven outpost.<BR>
<A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Frontier%20Mnts"><B>3. </B>Frontier Mtns.</A> - 2 different maps of this zone.<BR>
<A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Kunark"><B>4. </B>Kunark Zone Connections</A> - 2 nice Kunark zone maps.<BR>
<A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Skyfire%20Mtns"><B>5. </B>Skyfire Mtns.</A> - by Shadowwalker Stormmaster.<BR>
<A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Lake%20of%20Ill%20Omen"><B>6. </B>Lake of Ill Omen</A> - by Hoppas Ovale.<BR>
<A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Swamp%20of%20No%20Hope"><B>7. </B>Swamp of No Hope</A> - by Hoppas Ovale.<BR>
<A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Paineel"><B>8. </B>Paineel</A> - 2 maps by EQ Atlas which we didn't have before.<BR>
<A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Erudin"><B>9. </B>Erudin</A> - 2 maps by EQ Atlas.<BR>
<A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Erudin%20Palace"><B>10. </B>Erudin Palace</A> - by EQ Atlas.</FONT><BR><BR>

<B><I>MadWand</I></B><BR><BR>
